- `GReal t` is `(G.resToImagAxis t).re`

So, `FmodGReal t = ((F.resToImagAxis t).re) / ((G.resToImagAxis t).re)`

The goal is to show that `↑(FmodGReal t) = Function.resToImagAxis F t / Function.resToImagAxis G t`.

The left side `↑(FmodGReal t)` is the coercion of the real number `FmodGReal t` to a complex number. The right side is the division of two complex numbers, `Function.resToImagAxis F t` and `Function.resToImagAxis G t`.

